{TEXT 273 0 "" }}{SECT 0 {PARA 5 "" 0 "" {TEXT 321 20 " Governing equa
tion " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 320 47 "The governing equation solved i
s of the form :\n" }{TEXT 274 38 "theta(x)*dC/dt = -d(Fdiff+Fadv)/dx +
 R" }{TEXT 320 2 ",\n" }{TEXT 320 7 "where \n" }{TEXT 320 69 "- dX/dp \+
is the partial derivative of X with respect to p [M/L^3/[p]]\n" }{TEXT
 320 84 "- theta(x) = A(x)*por(x) for dissolved, and A(x)*(1-por(x)) f
or solid species [L^2]\n" }{TEXT 320 43 "- Fdiff = -(D(x)*theta(x)*dC/
dx) [M/L^2/T]\n" }{TEXT 320 34 "- Fadv  = (v*theta(x)*C)[M/L^2/T]\n" }
{TEXT 320 57 "- A is the cross section area [L^2], por is porosity [-]
\n" }{TEXT 320 49 "- v is the advection velocity [L/T], the sum of \n"
 }{TEXT 320 85 "the water flow velocity (vwat = water flow q in [L^3/T
]/theta(x), solutes only) and \n" }{TEXT 320 105 "an advective velocit
y w acting upon both solids and solutes (e.g. movement due to fixed re
ference frame)\n" }{TEXT 320 64 "- D is the effective diffusion coeffi
cient [L^2/T], the sum of \n" }{TEXT 320 59 "the molecular diffusion c
oefficient (Dmol, solutes only), \n" }{TEXT 320 39 "the bioturbation c
oefficient (Db) and \n" }{TEXT 320 73 "the dispersion coefficient (Dis
p = aL*|vwat|, solutes only, aL in [L]). \n" }{TEXT 320 101 "- R is th
e sum of the reaction terms [M/L^3/T] as specified in the reaction net
work established below" }}}{SECT 0 {PARA 5 "" 0 "" {TEXT 321 9 " Cavea
ts " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 320 60 "- for real numbers you should add
 a point after the number.\n" }{TEXT 320 30 "- make sure all units mat
ch. \n" }{TEXT 320 68 "e.g. rates and dXdt, or flux boundary condition
s and concentrations\n" }{TEXT 320 46 "for the conversion of solid to \+
solute units, \n" }{TEXT 320 76 "one may define temporary variables th
at can be used in the rate laws below:\n" }{TEXT 320 49 "s_dens := 2.5
; # solid density in [g/cm_solid^3]\n" }{TEXT 320 48 "sd := 1000. * s_
dens * (1. - por(j)) / por(j); \n" }{TEXT 320 66 "the factor 1.d03 con
verts cm^3 to liter, e.g. [g/cm^3] to [g/l]. \n" }{TEXT 320 40 "note t
hat you need to refer to porosity " }{TEXT 275 7 "exactly" }{TEXT 320 
11 " as por(j)." }}}}{SECT 0 {PARA 3 "" 0 "" {TEXT 322 21 " Physics - \+
Parameters" }}{PARA 206 "" 0 "" {TEXT 323 19 "The list of length " }
{TEXT 26 20 "nparphys & nparphys2" }{TEXT 323 13 " is given by " }
{TEXT 26 22 "phys_name & phys_name2" }{TEXT 323 26 "; the values colle
cted in " }{TEXT 26 21 "phys_val & phys_val2." }}{SECT 0 {PARA 5 "" 0 
"" {TEXT 321 33 " Spatial and temporal domain size" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 26 9 "tot_time:" }{TEXT 320 43 " total length of simulation (T, \+
e.g. years)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 26 10 "depth_max:" }{TEXT 320 60 
" spatial extent, e.g. total depth of simulation (L, e.g. cm)" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 20 "tot_time := 1.0e4 ;\n" }
{MPLTEXT 1 0 18 "depth_max := 0.1 ;" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 11 "" 
1 "" {XPPMATH 20 ">I)tot_timeG6\"$\"#5\"\"$" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 ">I*depth_maxG6\"$\"\"\"!\"\"" }}}}{SECT 0 {PARA 5 "" 0 ""
 {TEXT 321 23 " Transport coefficients" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT
 26 3 "vaL" }{TEXT 320 95 ": longitudinal dispersivity (L). The disper
sion coefficient is calculated as Disp = aL*|vwat| \n" }{TEXT 26 3 "vi
q" }{TEXT 320 82 ": depth dependency of flow. 0: constant, else changi
ng with depth (i.e. distance)\n" }{TEXT 26 3 "vq0" }{TEXT 320 53 ": wa
ter flow (either constant or else at x=0, L^3/T)\n" }{TEXT 26 3 "viw" 
}{TEXT 320 79 ": depth dependency of w. 0: constant, else changing wit
h depth (i.e. distance)\n" }{TEXT 26 3 "vw0" }{TEXT 320 89 ": advectio
n velocity working on solids and solutes (either constant or else at x
=0, L/T)\n" }{TEXT 26 4 "viDb" }{TEXT 320 80 ": depth dependency of Db
. 0: constant, else changing with depth (i.e. distance)\n" }{TEXT 26 
4 "vDb0" }{TEXT 320 97 ": bioturbation coefficient working on solids a
nd solutes (either constant or else at x=0, L^2/T)\n" }{TEXT 320 1 "\n
" }{TEXT 320 134 "- user specified profiles of q(x), w(x) or Db(x) mus
t be defined in the fortran subroutines advcoeff.f and diffcoeff.f, re
spectively.\n" }{TEXT 320 87 "- the molecular diffusion coefficients f
or the species used are specified further below" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> 
" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "val := 0.01 ;\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "viq := 0 ;
\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "vq0 := 0;\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "viw := 0 ;\n" }
{MPLTEXT 1 0 68 "vw0 := 1.0e-4 ; #in mm 10.0e-6*(1.4/Col_fac+(Col_fac-
1.0)/Col_fac);\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "viDb := 0 ;\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 13 "v
Db0 := 0.0 ;" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 ">I$va
lG6\"$\"\"\"!\"#" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 ">I$viqG6\"\"\"!" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 ">I$vq0G6\"\"\"!" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 ">I$viwG6\"\"\"!" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 ">I$vw0G6
\"$\"#5!\"&" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 ">I%viDbG6\"\"\"!" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 ">I%vDb0G6\"$\"\"!F&" }}}}{SECT 0 {PARA 5
 "" 0 "" {TEXT 321 40 " Porosity profile and cross section area" }}
